                                                                            GIT REBASE

 
 1> Git Rebase = git rebase moves or replays the commits of a feature branch
                 on top of the latest main branch .

    
    purpose :
  
   #> update the feature branch with the latest main branch.

   #> keep git history clean and linear.


 2> why do we use rebase ?

  #> get the latest changes from the main branch.
  #> keep git history clean.
  #> avoid unnecessary merge commits.
  #> reduce merge conflicts before creating a pull request.


 3> Git rebase 

 # commands
  
 #> git switch [branch name]
 #> git reabse main
 
  in conflicts occurs :

 #> nano app.txt
 #> git add app.txt
 #> git rebase --continue


 5> rebase conflicts

=  A rebase conflict occurs when git cannot automatically replay a commit 
   because the same line has been modified in both branches.

  steps to resolve

 #> open the conflicted file.
 #> remove conflict markers.
 #> save the correct content.
 #> stage the file = git add app.txt
 #> continue the rebase = git rebase --continue

 6> rebase command  
  
  start rebase main = start rebase
  git rebase --continue = continue after resolving conflicts.
  git rebase --skip = skip the current commit during rebase
  git rebase --abort = cancel the rebase and return to previous state 
